<subSubSection id="F50FECCBBE2025806AC6EE5AFC7998F7" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3170A8FD85B6518AB49DAED97734BD44" pageNumber="730">
Etymology Gr 
<taxonomicName id="12717DFF868DC96D20E8210E5EF76E54" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182062" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole pepo Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole pepo Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="730" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pepo">pepo</taxonomicName>
, melon, alluding to the unusual head shape of the major.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8B4229A41A01748D6126758CF472D0AA" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5150A9C10428D0C071D7D0A5A038BD21" pageNumber="730">
diagnosis A large, yellow member of the 
<taxonomicName id="E860131A60BF7C27FCD51657180B3EFF" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34070" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="730" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">tristis</taxonomicName>
group, similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2167229DEB1F3BBB42F5D929BBB6FF34" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182072" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole rotundiceps Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole rotundiceps Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="730" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundiceps">rotundiceps</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4529EA106A38EF72E5DFECE012632DAD" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182081" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole sphaerica Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole sphaerica Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="730" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphaerica">sphaerica</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="639D391F498425112B3C5E23917DB9DD" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182082" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole subsphaerica Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole subsphaerica Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="730" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subsphaerica">subsphaerica</taxonomicName>
, easily distinguished by the following traits.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8111A3C9A80F3A999219CFFD160DEB59" type="description">
<paragraph id="9A16473866764163D3938042B9A1ABA7" pageNumber="730">Major: head greatly swollen; clypeus and mandibles reduced proportionate to the head; outline of head in full-face view almost completely devoid of pilosity; in side view, profiles of both anterior dorsal half and anterior ventral half of head capsule densely pilose, but profiles of posterior dorsal and ventral halves bare of pilosity; propodeal spines long and acute. Minor: body slender; occiput narrowed, with nuchal collar; propodeal spines long and slender, i.e., needle-like. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.78, HL 1.66, SL 1.02, EL 0.22, PW 0.84. Paratype minor: HW 0.64, HL 0.80, SL 1.06, EL 0.16, PW 0.44.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B731ADF9FCF012D7A7CB73DDEBB91223" pageNumber="730">Color Major: head and appendages medium yellow; mesosoma, waist, and gaster yellowish brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8947749C225B47C9E8198BFBF8AF0316" pageNumber="730">Minor: concolorous dark yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="47DC8FAF8D47037EE7848522672BF2E6" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="CA065429580DC34F1A7E2127D51B1E6F" pageNumber="730">range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="132FA32FD0EAA3F566E7FD083D29C97E" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="CC9BDA43BF10CD77B550D3ADCDB95475" pageNumber="730">biology Collected in spiny bamboo (Guadua) forest.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="64A568D765D3F6BC9C832E87BA6D3A08" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="CCD42C3CCEC031BF4050C51DB129462D" pageNumber="730">Figure Upper: holotype, major. Lower: paratype, minor. COLOMBIA: Finca Los Guaduales, 10 km southwest of San Jose del Palmar, Rio Torito, Choco, 800 m (Charles Kugler). Scale bars = 1 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
